    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "respite care won't change the fact that i'm just slowing them all down... i see the way they look when the phone rings or when they have to drive over here. it's like they're just managing a task. if i wasn't here, they'd finally have their lives back. they could travel, be happy, not constantly worrying about if i've fallen or if my heart is acting up. wouldn't that be a better gift for them?",
